<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Bonita lifts interim shr, div.</title>
<headline>Bonita lifts interim shr, div.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1996-12-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended October 31, 1996</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     14.4	 vs     12.5</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 3.5	  vs     2.6</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   31.53	vs     26.65</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   48.64	vs     39.08</p>
<p>    Tax			 17.03	vs     12.43</p>
<p>    Finance costs	   2.54	 vs     0.55</p>
<p>    Turnover		  501.71     vs     473.21</p>
<p>Div payable Jan 17</p>
<p>on register Jan 10</p>
<p>Full name: Bonnita Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said it would make a capitalisation share award to shareholders registered at the close of business on December 13, 1996. Shareholders may elect to recieve a cash dividend instead.</p>
<p>The capitalisation shares will be calculated by multiplying the number of shares held by 3.7 divided by the weighted average share price of Bonnita on the three consecutive trading days ending December 12, 1996</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
</text>
